The Beach
programme.desc: Danny Boyle's film stars Leonard Di Caprio as Richard, a free-spirited traveller who ends up in Bangkok. Frustrated by the sameness of the western experience in the city, he is intrigued when traveller Daffy tells him of an island paradise. Equipped with a map, and accompanied by French couple Francoise and Etienne, the trio eventually find the titular beach, a commune benevolently ruled by Sal. But as Richard finds out, the real world, in all its violent forms, has a habit of intruding on even the most perfect idyll..

programme.title: Hard Candy
programme.desc: A 14-year-old girl (Ellen Page) and a thirtysomething photographer (Patrick Wilson) connect in an on-line chat room and arrange a meeting in this creepily provocative psychodrama that turns into an unsettling tale of retribution. Sandra Oh, Jennifer Holmes. Directed by David Slade

programme.title: Assassin's Creed
programme.desc: In this adaptation of the popular video-game series, a death-row convict relives his ancestor's memories as an assassin in 15th-century Spain. From this out-of-body experience, he gains the training he needs to battle a conspiracy in the present day

programme.title: New Jack City
programme.desc: Streetwise cops target a megalomaniacal drug lord, whose empire is threatened by an informer

programme.title: Invictus
programme.desc: "Invictus" tells the inspiring true story of how Nelson Mandela joined forces with the captain of South Africa's rugby team, Francois Pienaar to help unite their country. Newly elected President Mandela knows his nation remains racially and economically divided in the wake of apartheid. Believing he can bring his people together through the universal language of sport, Mandela rallies South Africa's underdog rugby team as they make an unlikely run to the 1995 World Cup Championship match

programme.title: Murder by Numbers
programme.desc: In this suspense film, Barbet Schroeder (Barfly) directs Sandra Bullock as a savvy homicide detective who matches wits with two high-school boys bent on taking a life for a thrill. Bullock, as detective Cassie Mayweather, has a new partner, Sam Kennedy (played by Ben Chaplin). Sam attempts to rein in his fiery partner, forcing her to play by the book. But Bullock and her young antagonists know that it's not about the book, it's all about the numbers. They are the key to solving this near perfect murder

programme.title: Dracula
programme.desc: Frank Langella infuses new blood---and sensual charm---into this umpteenth remake of Bram Stoker's classic. Laurence Olivier, Donald Pleasence, Kate Nelligan. Harker: Trevor Eve. Mina: Jan Francis. Directed by John Badham

programme.title: Annabelle
programme.desc: A group of orphaned girls are taken in by a doll maker and his wife, who are still grieving the death of their daughter. However, they are soon terrorized by a haunted doll that's lurking within the couple's house

programme.title: Hacksaw Ridge
programme.desc: Biopic about World War II Army medic Desmond Doss, a conscientious objector who refused to take a life or even carry a weapon. Doss was eventually awarded the Medal of Honor for saving the lives of 75 soldiers on the battlefields of Okinawa

programme.title: A Little Chaos
programme.desc: Romantic drama about Sabine de Barra, a gifted gardener and landscaper who is hired to design a section of the elaborate landscaping to be constructed at the palace of Versailles for Louis XIV. The job brings with it gender and class barriers, and she also must contend with renowned landscaper André Le Notre, with whom she develops both a professional and romantic relationship

programme.title: Funny People
programme.desc: A struggling stand-up comic befriends a movie star who's dealing with a serious illness and trying to win back the love of his life

programme.title: Driving Miss Daisy
programme.desc: A Southern matron forges a bond with her black chauffeur in the racially-divided 1960s South. Only when he is retired and she is confined to a home for the elderly do the two fully realize that they've been friends and kindred spirits all along

programme.title: Fargo
programme.desc: The Coen brothers' sly drama about a policewoman (Frances McDormand) who's trying to determine how several murders and a kidnapping are linked to an unassuming car salesman (William H. Macy). Showalter: Steve Buscemi. Grimsrud: Peter Stormare

programme.title: Love Potion No. 9
programme.desc: Two nerdy scientists become irresistible after drinking a palm reader's secret formula

programme.desc: Struggling actress Mia and aspiring jazz pianist Sebastian begin a whirlwind romance as they both pursue their dreams in Los Angeles. However, their blossoming relationship is challenged when their careers pull them in different directions

programme.title: Indian Summer
programme.desc: Ensemble tale about friends who reunite at a camp that's in danger of closing down. Alan Arkin, Matt Craven. Beth: Diane Lane. Belston: Bill Paxton. Jennifer: Elizabeth Perkins. Brad: Kevin Pollak. Stick Coder: Sam Raimi. Matthew: Vincent Spano. Written and directed by Mike Binder

programme.title: The Trouble with Spies
programme.desc: An inept secret agent searches for his missing colleague in Ibiza

programme.title: Away We Go
programme.desc: Bert (John Krasinski) and Verona (Maya Rudolph) are expecting a child. In the sixth month of pregnancy, the couple learns that Bert¿s parents are moving to Europe, and since having them around was the only reason for living in that town, they decide to try alternative places where they have no relatives or friends: Phoenix, Tucson, Wisconsin, Montreal and finally Miami. Away We Go, directed by Sam Mendes (Best Director Oscar-winner for American Beauty) and written by novelists Dave Eggers and Vendela Vida, is a road movie that portrays, along the way, the difficulties of raising and supporting a family

programme.title: Never Been Kissed
programme.desc: Drew Barrymore enchants as a Chicago newspaper editor who relives her hellish teen years while on an undercover assignment at a local high school. Barrymore's great, but the film celebrates the fact that her character wins over the same type of “in crowd” that taunted her as a teen. David Arquette costars as her cool brother. Raja Gosnell is the director, and Barrymore served as executive producer

programme.desc: A grizzled older cop is removed from a car theft case and partnered with a younger detective, but that doesn't stop him from interfering with the investigation, leaving his new partner stuck in between doing what's right and doing his job

programme.desc: A quirky crossword-puzzle constructor falls for a cameraman and follows him across the country in hopes of winning his heart

programme.desc: With the help of his stoner brother, a California scholar seeks an alternate route to Stanford when the usual college-admissions process doesn't work

programme.desc: A drug shipment is sent to the wrong address, prompting a frantic race to recover the package before its contents are discovered. Meanwhile, intended recipients Jesus and Chita attempt to track down the shipment before drug lord Bodego Diablo realizes it's missing. But Bodega already knows the score and he wants his drugs back

Meanwhile, intended recipients Jesus and Chita attempt to track down the shipment before drug lord Bodego Diablo realizes it's missing. But Bodega already knows the score and he wants his drugs back

programme.title: Extreme Ops

programme.title: The Alamo
programme.desc: With Dennis Quaid and Billy Bob Thornton in the cast, this historical drama features magnificent war scenes as it reconstructs the revolution over the independence of Texas, in 1836 –before, during and after the construction of the Alamo (a fort built by Spanish missionaries to catechize the natives). Texans and Tejanos (born in Mexico), led by William Travis, Davy Crockett (Thornton) and Jim Bowie, are besieged by an army commanded by Mexican dictator Antonio Lopez de Santa Ana. Later, however, the outcome of the battle of San Jacinto, under General Sam Houston (Dennis Quaid), is the defeat of the Santa Ana men, which finally leads to the independence of the state

Steamy action and gore galore ensue as the male student body succumbs to Jennifer's insatiable appetite for human flesh. Now it's up to her best friend (Amanda Seyfried) to stop Jennifer's reign of terror before it's too late!

But it soon becomes apparent that someone in their midst has an agenda of their own when, after the heist, they discover that the briefcase has been switched. (Including five News Update)

Remake of the 1962 thriller

programme.title: Invictus
programme.desc: "Invictus" tells the inspiring true story of how Nelson Mandela joined forces with the captain of South Africa's rugby team, Francois Pienaar to help unite their country. Newly elected President Mandela knows his nation remains racially and economically divided in the wake of apartheid. Believing he can bring his people together through the universal language of sport, Mandela rallies South Africa's underdog rugby team as they make an unlikely run to the 1995 World Cup Championship match

programme.title: The Medallion
programme.desc: A Hong Kong detective teams up with a British agent and an investigator to stop a global slave ring. Combining the martial arts prowess of international action superstar Jackie Chan with state-of-the-art special effects, The Medallion is an action comedy co-starring Claire Forlani, Lee Evans and Julian Sands. Chan plays Eddie Yang, a Hong Kong cop who suffers a near fatal accident while investigating a case involving a mysterious medallion. Eddie soon discovers that with the powerful medallion in his possession, he gains incredible speed, strength and skills, taking his martial arts abilities to awe-inspiring heights. Enlisting the help of an old flame, British Interpol agent Nicole James, Eddie is determined to learn the secret of the medallion and face down the evil crime lord Snakehead, who wants to use its awesome powers for his own nefarious plans

programme.title: Terminator Salvation
programme.desc: Director McG takes the helm for the fourth instalment of the sci-fi action franchise, starring Christian Bale and Sam Worthington. The principal action takes place in the not-too-distant 2018, in the devastated world that was glimpsed early in the series, where a determined group of resistance fighters are battling killing machines that are set on sole control of the planet. John Connor is one of the resistance leaders who discovers that their Skynet robot adversaries have a potentially fatal design flaw. They also learn that Skynet plans to imminently assassinate the top resistance leaders; Connor is second on the kill list to Kyle Reese, a civilian whose significance is known only to Connor. Meanwhile, Marcus Wright has also appeared on the scene - is he a mysterious warrior, out to defeat the machines, or does he have darker motives? Also starring Helena Bonham Carter, Bryce Dallas Howard and Moon Bloodgood

programme.title: Once upon a Time in Mexico
programme.desc: Third in the series of films featuring the heroic, guitar-toting hit man, El Mariachi. When a sinister drugs baron devises a plot to assassinate Mexico's president, a corrupt and unstable CIA agent hires the reclusive El Mariachi to thwart his plans, a task that he is willing to undertake for personal as well as professional reasons

programme.title: Speed
programme.desc: Keanu Reeves plays Jack Traven, a young cop working with the LAPD bomb squad. Thwarting mad bomber Howard Payne, who has wired up a lift to explode, Traven finds himself the object of revenge. Payne rigs a bomb to a bus which arms when the speed reaches above 50mph and explodes if it drops beneath. With passenger Annie Porter drafted in to replace the injured driver, Traven has to work out how to disarm the bomb and evacuate the passengers while she keeps the bus up to speed in urban LA. Jan de Bont's thriller piles on the action and even after Traven saves everyone on the bus, there's still a roller-coaster finale on a runaway subway train commandeered by Payne

programme.title: The Beach
programme.desc: Danny Boyle's film stars Leonard Di Caprio as Richard, a free-spirited traveller who ends up in Bangkok. Frustrated by the sameness of the western experience in the city, he is intrigued when traveller Daffy tells him of an island paradise. Equipped with a map, and accompanied by French couple Francoise and Etienne, the trio eventually find the titular beach, a commune benevolently ruled by Sal. But as Richard finds out, the real world, in all its violent forms, has a habit of intruding on even the most perfect idyll..

The objective is to create a legion of powerful soldiers to conquer Mars. But the experiment goes wrong and Banner's organism is affected by the gamma rays. programme.desc: In the mythical Middle-earth, a fantastic, mysterious world inhabited by men, Hobbits, wizards, elves, dwarfs and Trolls, lives Frodo Baggins (Elijah Wood), a shy Hobbit who must accomplish a difficult mission to save his land's destiny. It all begins when Frodo receives a ring from his uncle Bilbo (Ian Holm) and wizard Gandalf (Ian McKellen) discovers it is the Unique Ring itself. This powerful ring has been conceived by Sauron, the dark Lord of Mordor (Sala Baker), and with it, it is possible to enslave the whole of the Middle-earth through the use of dark forces. To destroy the ring, Frodo must take it to a distant mountain in Mordor, a region controlled by the Master of Evil. Fortunately, he is accompanied by a group formed by Hobbits Sam (Sean Astin), Merry (Dominic Monaghan) and Pippin (Billy Boyd), as well as Gandalf, the human warriors Aragorn (Viggo Mortensen) and Boromir (Sean Bean), and elf Legolas (Orlando Bloom). Together they have to confront dangerous obstacles in a frightening world of mystery and darkness. This spectacular adaptation of J.R.R. Tolkien's epic trilogy was directed by Peter Jackson

programme.title: Elizabeth I
programme.desc: A major new two-part Channel 4 drama by Nigel Williams, starring Helen Mirren, Jeremy Irons, Hugh Dancy, Ian McDiarmid and Patrick Malahide. The drama portrays 'The Virgin Queen' in her later years, exposing the conflict between her sense of duty and the instincts of her heart, her doomed affair with the Earl of Essex and the struggles of a powerful and independent woman battling to survive in a male dominated world. Part one of Elizabeth I focuses on her relationship with The Earl of Leicester, her lover and trusted advisor. Specifically, the story traces the evolution of their relationship as Leicester tries to balance his love for Elizabeth, his loyalty to her as her trusted advisor and his pursuit of his own self interests. Elizabeth and Leicester have agreed that they cannot marry - this would be strategically unwise for Elizabeth - but they have nevertheless chosen to remain on intimate terms with one another in spite of Leicester's role as advisor to the Queen. When a French prince/suitor, Anjou, arrives on the scene, Leicester initially sees him as a political threat and slowly comes to see him as an emotional threat as well. Their relationship also forms the prism through which the two other major events of this part of Elizabeth I's reign are viewed: the execution of Mary Queen of Scots and the War with Spain. Part One culminates with the death of Leicester and the British victory over Spain, juxtaposing Elizabeth's public celebration and private grief

programme.desc: Matt Reeves' smart monster thriller has been favourably compared to The Blair Witch Project , with which it shares the concept of using "found" camcorder footage to reveal its horrors. The film opens at a party for Manhattan yuppie Rob Hawkins where the revelries are interrupted by a loud explosion. As he and his friends Hud, Jason, Marlena and Lily emerge onto the street, the head of the Statue of Liberty cartwheels past them. Something very big, scaly and angry is trashing the city, and one of the targets is a high-rise where Beth, Rob's girlfriend lives. The group set out in a rescue bid, with Hud recording everything as they make their way through what has become a nightmarish New York, threatened both by the monster (only ever half-glimpsed, making it even more terrifying) and the parasitic lice it sheds, which develop a taste for human flesh. Will all, or indeed any, of the group make it to safety? The footage tells their stories in shocking, handheld detail in this superbly paced movie
